&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Animation Assistant Technical Director&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sony Pictures Imageworks is located on the unceded traditional territory of the Musqueam, Squamish, and Tsleil-Waututh First Nations. We are committed to respecting traditional lands, and working with communities towards reconciliation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sony Pictures Imageworks Canada Inc.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;658 Homer Street., Suite 405, Vancouver, BC, V6B 2R4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Language in work environment - English&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits per company policy: include healthcare, tuition reimbursement, RRSP&#39;s, Sick and Vacation leave, standard increases as applicable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Reporting to the Pipeline Supervisor and Technical Supervising Animator, as well as the HOCA and Supervising Animators on their designated production, an Animation Associate Technical Director (Anim ATD) will be involved in the creation, development and ongoing support of a high-end animation pipeline and pipeline workflows.&lt;br&gt;Their main focus is improved efficiency and optimization of animation workflows and tools, as well as prototyping tools, and utilities to support the animation team.&lt;br&gt;This is a service-oriented role, working between productions and development, and the Anim ATD should have a helpful, proactive and accommodating personality. Candidates should have a strong passion for animation and computer graphics, bringing artistic visions to life with a focus on creative problem solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Specifics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize animation workflows by leveraging automation and defining best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work alongside other show anim ATDs to assist the team in optimizing and reducing scene or workflow complexities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with the Supervising Animators to proactively implement optimizations for sequences or assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain scripts, tools and utilities for the animation team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in and understand the Imageworks’ proprietary animation pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help author tool or workflow specific training materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist artists with technical issues anywhere in the production pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the pipeline department to evaluate and support best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify workflow inefficiencies and work with artists and the pipeline teams to build scripts, tools and/or systems to improve them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide regular updates to the Supervising Animators and Pipeline Supervisor on progress, and challenges on the production.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate progress and challenges to the Animation HOD, Technical Supervising Animator, and animation development team, providing show context when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in support chats, spotlights and department meetings, ensuring a broad understanding of best practices, workflows and tools in the animation team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other departments to address creative and technical dependencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Supervising Animators on best practices and proactively help them solve sequence or asset related issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interest in Visual Development, Film, Animation and general computer graphics is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good Knowledge of Maya. Unreal Engine and Houdini are a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Programming experience in Python.&lt;/li&gt;
