&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As an Associate Media Engineer, you will participate in projects utilizing new technologies in the areas of content creation, viewing and delivery. You will help engineer solutions as needed by production, as well as helping to configure, deploy and support desktop, review and meeting hardware needs for visual effects and animation workflow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education, Qualifications and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Formal Education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in a related field (e.g., Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Multimedia, or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professional Certifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certifications in Media engineering or related fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary areas of responsibility will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install, configure, remove, and maintain media infrastructure services, hardware, and system software according to standard procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and calibrate audio/video systems, including review projection systems, video conferencing, media playback, device controls, and complex switching systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain meticulous records of all installed and removed hardware and software components, in addition to documentation for existing operational methods and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of installation procedures, standards, and the overall availability management process, by (including but not limited to) using standard procedures and diagnostic tools to test installations, correct problems, and document results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, measure, and report on media infrastructure load, performance, and security events, and promptly resolve identified operational issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out system media software maintenance tasks, and automate routine system administration tasks to specifications using standard tools and basic scripting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform preventative maintenance, handle backups/restores, and optimize system availability and reliability to meet service level targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the availability management process and its operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the assessment of media designs, specifications, and requirements in order to design comprehensive test cases and scripts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize established protocols to define and execute both manual and automated media testing procedures. Enhance testing efficiency by developing automated tasks and expanding test coverage through existing or new media infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and report on test results, issues, and risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with handling routine day-to-day communication with vendors and with collecting supplier performance data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist users with general IT troubleshooting and hardware deployments, and provide backup coverage for basic Service Desk and Desktop Support duties during team absences (with support from the remote Global Service Desk).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
